race.comment: Keen to play here with a couple that might represent good value. WORSFOLD (1) ran a blinder at a huge price last start when stepping out for the new stable for the first time. He's got a big weight to carry here but that's because he drops in class. He should get all the favours under Pannell from a kind draw. He can win. FALAISE (4) is drawn wide and might have to concede a start but he looks ready to peak third-up. Both of his runs this campaign have contained merit and suspect he will be finishing powerfully. RECIPROCAL (8) is another likely improver after being too bad to be true last time. Forgive the horse a bad run and take on his better form from last campaign. BALISTIQUE (11) is a local that can finish in the money.
